<div class="section-info-bio">
	<div class="shell">
	<div class="firsttext-wrapper">
	<div class="text-content-demo">
				<h1>Live Demo</h1>
				<p class="justify">This <a href="#" target="_blank">link</a> is a live demonstration of KOSAR with MySQL and a
<a href="http://www.bgbenchmark.org">social networking benchmark</a>
that emulates 300 simultanoues users performing
interactive social networking actions such as view a member
profile, invite a member to be friends, accept a pending friend
invitation, list friends, and others.</p>
			</div><!-- /.text-content-demo -->
			</div><!--/firsttext-wrapper-->
			<div class="Demo-questionsimg">
				<h3 id="head1">Why should I care?</h3>
								<div class="text-wrapper-demo">
									<div class="text-content-demo">
				<p class="justify" >The <strong>Performance Metrics</strong> tab shows the number of queries processed
by KOSAR per unit of time.
This page is shown to the left;
the circled area highlights the number of queries processed
per unit of time.
One may turn KOSAR and off (using the <strong>Setting</strong> tab of the live demo)
to see what happens.
When KOSAR is turned on, the system can process a large number of
queries per unit of time.  Once KOSAR is turned off, performance
diminishes greately.</p>
									</div><!-- /.text-content-demo -->
								</div><!--text-wrapper-demo-->
				<div class="text-wrapper-demo">
					<div class="text-content-demo">
						<h3>What else can I do?</h3>
				<p class="justify">The KOSAR interface enables its users to see the query templates that
are cached, see the <strong>Cached Queries</strong> tab of the live demo.
KOSAR is caching instance of those templates with unselected radio
buttons. 
By selecting the radio button of a query template and clicking Submit,
the user notifies KOSAR to stop caching instances of the selected
template.
Double clicking a selected query template turns its radio
button off.
By clicking Submit, caching of query instances of the template is
re-enabled. </p>
					</div><!-- /.text-content-demo -->
				</div><!--/text-wrapper-text-->
				<div class="text-wrapper-demo">
					<div class="text-content-demo">
							<h3>Is there more?</h3>
				<p class="justify">Yes, one may also preview the application's last 100 SQL queries
by navigating to the <strong>Last 100 Queries</strong> tab of the interface.
The <strong>Last 100 Insert/Delete/Update</strong> tab shows the update commands
issued by the application.  KOSAR caches the result of SQL
queries.  SQL Insert/Delete/Update command invalidate the
impacted cached query results.  </p>
<br>
<p class="justify">Finally, the <strong>SQL Stats</strong> tab shows the statistics of the different query
templates such as their cache hit rate and their frequency.  A query
template with a higher frequency constitutes a larger portion of the
system workload</p>
			</div><!-- /.text-content -demo-->
			</div><!--/text-wrapper-demo-->
			<div class="text-content-demo">
				<h3>Is this the complete interface of KOSAR?</h3>
				<p>No, this demo is showcasing the client interface of KOSAR.
An application may consist of tens of clients (e.g., Web Servers)
and each may employ KOSAR to enhance performance.
Each client will have an interface similar to the live demo.
These clients are coordinated using KOSAR Core. 
KOSAR CORE has a similar interface that is not demonstrated here.</p>
			</div><!-- /.text-content -demo-->
			</div><!--/firsttext-wrapper-->
			</div><!--Demo-questionsimg-->
